  "text": "The HTTP connection manager route matching implementation in Envoy is found in the following key components:\n\n**Virtual Host Selection and Route Matching Algorithm** (source/common/router/config_impl.cc and config_impl.h):\nThe core routing logic is implemented in the RouteMatcher class which performs virtual host selection via the findVirtualHost() method. This method searches for a matching virtual host by examining the request's authority header against configured virtual host domains. It supports exact matches, wildcard prefixes (e.g., *.example.com), wildcard suffixes (e.g., sub-*.example.com), and a default virtual host fallback. The method findWildcardVirtualHost() handles the longest-wildcard matching algorithm to prioritize more specific matches.\n\nOnce a virtual host is selected, the VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries() method iterates through the routes in that virtual host and uses the Matchable interface (implemented by RouteEntryImplBase and its subclasses like PrefixRouteEntryImpl and PathRouteEntryImpl) to match against request headers, paths, methods, and other criteria. The getRouteFromRoutes() method provides a callback-based matching approach for routes with matcher trees.\n\n**HTTP Connection Manager Route Caching** (source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc and conn_manager_impl.h):\nThe ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStream class manages route caching via the route() method, which caches the matched route for the duration of the request to ensure stable routing decisions. The setCachedRoute() and refreshCachedRoute() methods handle cache invalidation when headers are modified by filters.\n\n**Route Action Dispatch** (source/common/router/router.cc and router.h):\nThe Router filter's decodeHeaders() method retrieves the cached route from the connection manager and dispatches to the appropriate route action (cluster selection, redirect, direct response, etc.). The router filter also manages upstream request creation and cluster selection based on the matched route.\n\n**Supporting Components**:\n- source/common/router/config_utility.cc: Utilities for route configuration processing\n- source/common/router/rds_impl.cc: Route configuration provider for dynamic route updates\n- source/common/router/vhds.cc: Virtual host dynamic subscription for on-demand virtual host loading\n- source/common/router/scoped_config_impl.cc: Scoped routing for multi-tenant configurations\n- source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc: HTTP connection manager factory and configuration\n- source/extensions/filters/http/router/config.cc: Router filter factory and configuration"
}

